  "prompt": "How much did it cost to build Walt Disney World?",
  "response": "The construction of Walt Disney World, located in Florida, began in 1967 and the park officially opened on October 1, 1971. The project was massive and involved creating not just the Magic Kingdom theme park, but also infrastructure, hotels, and other amenities. The initial cost to build Walt Disney World was approximately $400 million. This covered the creation of the original Magic Kingdom park, the Contemporary Resort, the Polynesian Village Resort, and other associated developments. This figure, while substantial at the time, laid the foundation for what would become one of the world's premier vacation destinations.",
